title: Kenya, Ghana first to ratify continental free-trade deal
description:
Kenya and Ghana have made history as the first countries to ratify the African Continental Free-Trade Area agreement. Chairperson of the African Union Commission, Moussa Faki Mahamat, says it's vital that other members follow suit.  CGTN's Girum Chala has more.
